        <font size='4'><b>INTERNATIONAL GUITAR MONTH STRIKES A CHORD IN MILLSBERRY</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20090402.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, April  2, 2009</b> &mdash;
    Are you amped for April? Well, get ready because it&#039;s International <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Guitar Month</a>, and Millsberry&#039;s guitar owners are tuning their strings and getting set to rock.<br><br>Like us, readers may not have heard of this month-long event. However, the celebration has been around for quite some time&mdash;not as long as the modern guitar itself, which has been around for thousands of years&mdash;and is celebrated worldwide. One source explained that the idea behind International Guitar Month is to promote a <i>whole month of pure guitar indulgence</i>: lessons, concerts, festivals, the works.<br><br>And how will Millsberry get down? With a little help from Darren Lancaster, lead singer of the Wheels band, and genuine guitar guru. For our interview, we found him clad in black leather <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=1">pants and a black leather jacket</a>, inside his studio, hanging with the rest of his band.<br>
<br>
<i><i>Gazette</i></i>: &quot;Darren! We are so excited to have you back in Millsberry. What do you have in store for us to help celebrate your favorite event of the year?&quot;<br><br><i>Darren</i>: &quot;We&#039;ll be having mini concerts every week as we finish our new album.  Some shows will be at <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Toys, Tricks, and Games</a>, and <a href="http://millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a>. And we&#039;ll finish off the month with the completed album, Through the Mill and Back. All in all, I&#039;ve just been happy <i>shredding</i> with my band!&quot;<br><br><i><i>Gazette</i></i>: &quot;Everyone is going to be jazzed about that! Why don&#039;t you tell us a little more about <i>shredding</i>?&quot;<br><br><i>Darren</i>: &quot;Oh, it&#039;s just rockin&#039; out as fast you can on the electric guitar! Wanna try?&quot;<br><br><i><i>Gazette</i></i>: &quot;Ha! Do you have earplugs? So&mdash;what was your first guitar?&quot;<br><br><i>Darren</i>: &quot;A little plastic ukulele, when I was seven. I would play it and pretend I was in Hawaii. Then, when I finally made it to Hawaii, on tour, I bought my favorite &quot;guitar&quot; of all&mdash;a <i>keytar</i> [see picture]!&quot;<br><br><i><i>Gazette</i></i>: &quot;Oh, come on, Darren. You can&#039;t play an instrument with no strings attached&mdash;not this month!&quot;<br><br><i>Darren</i>: &quot;Ha! Not even an air guitar? Anyway, I just think everyone should have the opportunity to learn an instrument&mdash;and the guitar is one of the easiest to pick up.&quot;<br><br>Well, you heard it from our very own guitar hero&mdash;International Guitar Month is in full swing. Get ready to tango, flamenco, and rock out. And who knows? Millsberry may never be the same again, thanks to this wild month-long jam. Can you already hear that out-of-tune strumming?!<br>
    </div>

